body:
For context, the following code triggers the private-in-public lint:

```rust
pub mod inner {
    pub type Alias = Impl<A>;

    struct A;
    pub struct Impl<T>(T);
}
```

Producing this kind of error:
> warning: private type `A` in public interface (error E0446)

I tried this code:

```rust
pub mod outer {
    mod inner {
        pub type Alias = Impl<A>;

        pub struct A;
        pub struct Impl<T>(T);
    }
    pub use inner::Alias;
    pub use inner::Impl;
}
```

I used: `rustc sample.rs --edition 2018 --crate-type=lib`

I expected to see this happen: a warning about the exposed inner types, as the structs in question have not been made pub and are inside a private module, yet their aliases are publicly accessible.

Instead, this happened: Nothing.

